sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K395706
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: rbs+crtZW under pBad promoter for double plasmids
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
CrtZ comes from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) (Accession number D90087), a type of Gram negative Enterobacteriaceae.
CrtW comes from Brevundimonas sp. strain SD212 (MBIC 03018) (Accession number AB377271).
.
This Composite Biobrick is created by standard assembly of Part BBa_I0500, Part BBa_I742158 and Part BBa_K395705.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part contains crtZW, which works as the astaxanthin biosynthesis pathway when add beta-carotene as a substrate.
It is necessary to add either beta-carotene or the synthesis operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
・This operon is under arabinose inducible promoter.
・I used this part with beta-carotene synthesis operon (BBa_K274210) as double plasmids in the project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yumiko Kinoshita

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rbs+crtZ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: crtZ (beta-carotene hydroxylase) from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087. Part of the carotenoid biosynthesis pathway. Converts beta-carotene to the yellow pigment zeaxnathin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was made as a single biobrick rather than separate rbs and coding sequence, hence the use of blunt combination to generate the final sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yumiko Kinoshita

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J15001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: strong synthetic E. coli ribosome binding site with SacI site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a strong synthetic E. coli ribosome binding site. It is synthesised as two complementary oligonucleotides rather than being incorporated into a biobrick plasmid. It incorporates a SacI site overlapping the XbaI site, which is preserved when it is added to any other biobrick. This allows easy detection of the RBS after it has been added upstream of a biobrick coding sequence in a plasmid vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Note the presence of a SacI site overlapping the XbaI site, which is preserved when this biobrick is added to any other biobrick. At the time of writing, this biobrick is added as a short piece of DNA composed of two complementary oligonucleotides rather than being incorporated into a biobrick cloning vector by itself. It can be added upstream of a biobrick coding sequence, and its presence can easily be detected in miniprep DNA on a gel by using a SacI-SpeI or similar digest.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French
